channel.title: Alright seriously, WHAT THE HELL
channel.description:
Working on gfx on players, when I add offsetY and offsetX I get this: [code] client.java:17307: offsetX is already defined in parseIncomingPackets() int offsetX = (absX - EnemyX2) * -1; ^ client.java:17308: offsetY is already defined in parseIncomingPackets() int offsetY = (absY - EnemyY2) * -1; ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 2 errors Press any key to continue . . . [/code] But when I don't add them I get this. [code] client.java:15984: cannot find symbol symbol : variable offsetY location: class client GraphicsHandler.createNormalSpell(-1, absY, absX, offsetY, ^ client.java:15985: cannot find symbol symbol : variable offsetX location: class client offsetX, 50, 95, 360, sp ellHeight,
Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 2 errors Press any key to continue . . . [/code] So what happens is basically...when I don't have it, it says I need it; but when I have it, it says I already have it. WHAT THE HELL?
